<div id="outline-container-org628e18c" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="org628e18c">Windows 10</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org628e18c">
</div>
<div id="outline-container-orgeb304b4" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="orgeb304b4">Download the <a href="https://github.com/TomerAberbach/mano-simulator/releases/download/mano-simulator-1.0-SNAPSHOT/mano-simulator-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar">mano-sim jar</a></h3>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org9fee71a" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org9fee71a">Download the exe  for <a href="https://www.oracle.com/java/technologies/downloads/#java11-windows">Java11</a></h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org9fee71a">
<p>
You might have to make an oracle account
</p>

<p>
The installer will download the binary to your program files by default.  Either way find out where the bin is stored.
</p>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org6d8a603" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org6d8a603">Run cmd as the administrator.</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org6d8a603">
<p>
Type in this command to set the JAVA HOME system variable.  The path should be to your java 11 bin files.
</p>

<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-shell">
setx JAVA_HOME -m <span style="font-style: italic;">"c:\Program Files\Java\jdk-11.0.13\bin"</span>

</pre>
</div>

<p>
restart the command prompt and check if the environment variable is set with
</p>

<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-shell">
<span style="font-weight: bold;">echo</span> %JAVA_HOME%

</pre>
</div>

<p>
this should output the path to the bin files
</p>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org2e6f35c" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org2e6f35c">Change your directory with cd to arrive where the mano-sim jar is installed</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org2e6f35c">
<p>
run
</p>
<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-shell">
java -jar mano-simulator-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar

</pre>
</div>

<p>
Th GUI should pop up and be ready to run
</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-orge66549f" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="orge66549f">Linux (Ubuntu 20.04)</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-orge66549f">
</div>
<div id="outline-container-org8174b7a" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org8174b7a">Install the default JDK</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org8174b7a">
<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-shell">
sudo apt update
  sudo apt install default-jdk


</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org365b76a" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org365b76a">Check the version is 11</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org365b76a">
<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-shell">
java --version

</pre>
</div>

<p>
Should have a similar output
</p>

<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-shell">
openjdk 11.0.11 2021-04-20
OpenJDK Runtime Environment (build 11.0.11+9-Ubuntu-0ubuntu2.20.04)
OpenJDK 64-Bit Server VM (build 11.0.11+9-Ubuntu-0ubuntu2.20.04, mixed mode)

</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org04920cd" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org04920cd">Install the simulator</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org04920cd">
<p>
Find out where you want to install the simulator
</p>

<p>
Install it with the following
</p>

<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-shell">
wget https://github.com/TomerAberbach/mano-simulator/releases/download/mano-simulator-1.0-SNAPSHOT/mano-simulator-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar

</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-orgfffbb76" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="orgfffbb76">Run the program</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-orgfffbb76">
<p>
You can now run the jar with
</p>

<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-shell">
java -jar mano-simulator-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar

</pre>
</div>

<p>
The simulator GUI should pop up at this point and be ready to run.
</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
